<HL>
   Business Brief -- Northern Telecom Ltd.:
   Firm to Spend $100 Million
   To Build New R&amp;D Site
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   NT BCE
</CO>
<LP>
   Northern Telecom Ltd. as expected said it will spend $100
million to build a new research and development facility to
house its R&amp;D operations in the Ottawa area.
   The new site will be built next to Northern's main Bell
Northern Research Center in Nepean, Ontario, bringing total
R&amp;D floor space to 1.3 million square feet. It will be used
to house satellite operations that are currently leasing
offices in the Ottawa area.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Northern currently employs 4,400 workers in its Ottawa R&amp;D
operations and is expected to add several thousand more to
the operation over the next 10 years. Its other R&amp;D sites
include Raleigh, N.C.; Atlanta; Richardson, Texas; and
Maidenhead, outside London.
</TEXT>
